article.headline: Bowling Green 83, Buffalo 70
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Brian Moten scored 20 points and Otis Polk had 13 points and 10 rebounds to lead Bowling Green to an 83-70 win over Buffalo on Thursday night. Buffalo (6-9, 0-3 Mid-American Conference) led early in the game, but Bowling Green (7-8, 2-1) dominated the Bulls in the first half, building a 43-26 lead at the break. The Falcons didn't trail in the second period and shot 53.8 percent for the game. Andrew Atman and Kambi Laleye each scored 11 points for Buffalo. Calvin Betts added 10 points and seven rebounds for the Bulls. Darryl Clements and Joe Jakubowski each scored 13 points for Bowling Green.
